.TH delete-dictionary 2
.XI delete-dictionary - "Remove a spelling dictionary from memory"
.SH NAME
delete-dictionary \- Remove a spelling dictionary from memory
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.I n
.B delete-dictionary
["\fIdictionary\fR"]
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B delete-dictionary
removes the given  \fIdictionary\fR  from memory,  where  \fIn\fR is a bitwise
flag determining the removal mode, defined as follows:-
.IP \fB0x01\fR
Prompt the user before loosing any changes (except to the ignore dictionary).
.IP \fB0x02\fR
Delete all the dictionaries other than the ignore dictionary.
.IP \fB0x04\fR
Delete the ignore dictionary.
.PP
If the  argument  does  not  have  bit 0x02 or 0x04  set,  which  specify  the
dictionaries  to be deleted, the user is prompted for the  "\fIdictionary\fR".
The default argument is 1.
.SH NOTES
The ignore  dictionary  is a  temporary  dictionary  that exists in memory for
duration  of the \*(mS  session;  the  dictionary  holds  words that have been
ignored during any previous spell checks (see
.Ht spell 2 ).
All of the words that have been ignored may be discarded with:-
.Me $emf-scheme
.CS
4 delete-dictionary
.CE
.Me $ehf-scheme
i.e. \fB\*(eS 4 \*ex\ delete-dictionary\fR.
